    "title": "Carrier India is Hiring: Quality Control Engineer (Senior)",
    "description": "Carrier India has an exciting opening for a Quality Control Engineer at our Howrah office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Carrier India:\nCarrier India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in 5S\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Howrah, West Bengal, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Carrier India!",
